@DilumAluthge That's a good point, but `ReactiveX` name will also lead to confusion with existing [JuliaGizmos/Reactive.jl](https://github.com/JuliaGizmos/Reactive.jl) package (which looks abandoned and provides less functionality).

[ReactiveX](https://github.com/ReactiveX) is a collection of repositories with reactive extensions for several languages. They use the same naming convention: `Rx` + language name, which in case  of Julia results in exactly `Rx.jl`.

Reactive community is quite big nowadays and in my opinion it is better to follow the established naming convention. Abbreviation `Rx` can also mean medical prescription, but in the context of  software development `Rx` is commonly used for reactive frameworks. As an example, google query "rx github" results in only reactive extension frameworks.
